  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Slice the eggplant, zucchini, red bell pepper, and onion into 1-inch pieces.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the coconut oil, miso paste, dried thyme, and dried oregano.",
    "Add the sliced vegetables to the bowl and toss to coat with the marinade.",
    "Transfer the vegetables to a baking sheet and roast for 20 minutes, or until tender.",
    "While the vegetables are roasting, slice the baguette into 1-inch pieces and toast in the oven for 5 minutes, or until lightly browned.",
    "In a small saucepan, heat the Brazilian Churrasco Sauce over low heat.",
    "Once the vegetables are done roasting, add them to the saucepan with the Churrasco Sauce and toss to coat.",
    "Spoon the vegetables and sauce over the toasted baguette, followed by the sliced Kalamata olives, Parmesan cheese, and fresh parsley.",
    "Garnish with sesame seeds and coconut cream, and serve hot.",
    "Garnish with salt to taste.",
    "Serve immediately, and enjoy!"
  ],
